reviews.review: ROS is not a good movie, but I expect it will make Disney a lot of money. In fact, it is cowardly — afraid to say or do anything new, unique or innovative. It’s professionally put together but visually bland, fast paced but somehow boring, overstuffed yet empty and unwilling to slow down and find anything resembling joy. Mostly it’s unimaginative, corporate board room approved pablum filled to the brim with lowest common denominator fan service, recycling plot points and plagiarizing from better films as it checks a box, checks another, points at a reference, ad nauseam for two plus hours. There’s little in the way of humor, emotion, character development or internal conflict, just a series of predictable MacGuffin chases before the inevitable victory hugs preceding the ending credits. Totally safe and totally forgettable. I’ll be “lightspeed skipping” ahead to another, better movie.
Felt like a rushed scavenger hunt but the chemistry between Rey and Kylo made up for most of it.
Rushed, horrible plot. Rian Johnston didnt give JJ Abrams much to work with after ruining the Last Jedi.
Best Star Wars movie by far!
It was definitely the best movie in the trilogy. There was just too much going on and gaps in the movie. Could have done better with captivating It’s audience.
It's a great ending to the Star Wars saga. As a fan, I'm satisfied.

I haven’t enjoyed any of the other 2 movies made in this new line. it’s very obvious that Disney could tell that they had up to this point put out 2 sub par movies (the last Jedi) being by far the worst star wars movie ever made. With the Rise of Skywalker I believe they tried to appease their unhappy core fan base. The movie is clearly put together to answer questions and address problems created by prior movies. It will not make everyone happy because for some reason some people actually enjoyed the last Jedi, this movie seemed to do all it could to counteract mistakes made in it. I would recommend the movie to the core fan base like me.
The inclusion of Palpatine was a horrible idea, none of the characters see any lessons learned or growth like in TLJ, the breakneck pacing hinders the film, just overall bad execution from JJ.
It’s Star Wars! You’re going to die some day. Enjoy the pretty colors and awesome music.
